# 🌐 HTML Medium Level Projects Repository

This contains ** medium-level HTML projects/questions** designed to take your HTML skills beyond the basics and help you build real-world webpage structures.

---

## 🎯 Objective

The purpose of this is to improve practical understanding of HTML by working on structured layouts, multi-page websites, forms, and UI-based web pages. These projects help bridge the gap between beginner and intermediate web development.

---

## 📚 List of Medium-Level HTML Projects

1. Responsive Personal Portfolio Page  
2. Multi-page Website (Home, About, Contact with navigation links)  
3. Student Registration Form with HTML validation attributes  
4. Product Listing Page (E-commerce style cards layout)  
5. Resume / CV Webpage (structured professional format)  
6. Login + Signup Pages with navigation between them  
7. Blog Page Layout (articles with sidebar structure)  
8. Navigation Bar with dropdown menu  
9. Contact Form with proper input types (email, phone, textarea)  
10. Image Gallery Grid Layout  
11. Student Result Sheet Table (structured and styled)  
12. Embedded YouTube Video with description section  
13. Product Landing Page (hero section + call-to-action button)  
14. Feedback Form (rating system, radio buttons, textarea)  
15. Simple Dashboard Layout (header, sidebar, main content area)

---

## 🧠 What You Will Learn

By building these projects, you will learn:

- Structuring multi-section web pages  
- Creating multi-page websites using links  
- Designing forms with better input handling  
- Building real-world UI layouts using HTML  
- Organizing content like blogs, dashboards, and landing pages  
- Improving semantic understanding of HTML structure  

